author: brane
msg: Add new files for "svn copy" to the Win32 build.
And fix mucho weirdness: Whoever added feedback.c to clients/cmdlune,
botched the .dsp change -- the file got added to the libsvn_client
project file. We didn't notice because we're building statically
linked libraries on Windows.
* libsvn_wc/libsvn_wc.dsp: Add copy.c
* libsvn_client/libsvn_client.dsp: Add copy.c. Remove ../clients/cmdline/
feedback.c.
* cmdline/subversion_client.dsp: Add copy-cmd.c and feedback.c.

author: sussman
msg: Partial revert/rewrite of commit #200.
Let's allow prop-files to exist that contain no props;  let's just
wrap a detector around it.  A better solution, suggested by kfogel.
* props.c (svn_wc__save_prop_file): if hash is empty, go ahead write a
pseudo-empty file out again.  no need to delete the file.
(svn_wc__do_property_merge):  revert to rev 200;  no need to remove
psuedo-empty property-files.
(svn_wc_prop_set):  same.
* questions.c (svn_wc_props_modified_p): rewrite to use new helper.
(empty_props_p):  new helper.  decides a prop-file is "empty" if
it's either non-existent or is of size 4 bytes or less ("END").
